@startuml mmap-component
title RosalindDB query path with FAISS mmap

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam NoteFontSize 10
skinparam wrapWidth 200

actor "client" as client

component "cp\n(Control Plane,\npublic origin)" as cp
component "query_dp\n(Query Data Plane;\nFAISS cache + mmap'd index)" as dp
database "cache_dir\n(local SSD,\nCACHE_DIR)" as cachedir
cloud "object_store\n(S3-compatible)" as os

client -down-> cp : HTTPS\nPOST /v1/query
cp -down-> dp : internal HTTP proxy\n(loopback in self-host,\nprivate net in prod)

dp -right-> os : GET shard.bin via _ensure_cached\n[on cache miss only]
dp -down-> cachedir : write file, atomic rename\n[on cache miss only]
dp -down-> cachedir : mmap(2) open\n[cheap, no I/O]
dp -down-> cachedir : page faults during index.search\n[on-demand, kernel reads touched pages]

note right of os
  WAN cost: paid once per shard.
  Skipped entirely on a cache hit.
end note

note right of cachedir
  Three distinct interactions:
  - one-time write on miss
  - cheap mmap open (offset table only)
  - on-demand page faults during search
  Must be a real local filesystem;
  never a FUSE object-store mount.
end note

note left of dp
  In-process _SHARD_CACHE keys by shard_id.
  Under RB_FAISS_MMAP=true the cached
  entry is the mmap-backed FAISS object
  plus the parsed sidecar; the byte
  accounting falls back to a fixed
  _MMAP_INDEX_ESTIMATE_BYTES (32 MiB)
  because resident bytes are the kernel's
  page cache, not the Python heap.
end note

note bottom of cp
  Trusts request after authenticating;
  injects X-RB-Tenant-Id for the DP.
end note

@enduml
